<title type="html"><![CDATA[8/18(Thu)What Causes Hunger? It's Not What You Think/Spain plans to control food waste (Host: May)]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/viewtopic.php?t=644&amp;p=669#p669"><![CDATA[
8/18(Thu)What Causes Hunger? It's Not What You Think/Spain plans to control food waste (Host: May)<br /><br />Agenda:<br />7:00-7:05 pm Opening Remarks<br />7:05-7:40 pm Session 1: Group Discussion<br />7:40-8:00 pm Individual Presentation<br />8:00-8:05 pm Break<br />8:05-8:40: Session 2: Group Discussion<br />8:40-9:00 pm Individual Presentation<br /><br />We will hold a zoom meeting only.<br /><br />Zoom meeting: Please click the link below<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://zoomtw.zoom.us/j/92987266213?pw">https://zoomtw.zoom.us/j/92987266213?pw</a><!-- m --> ...<br />Meeting ID:929 8726 6213<br />Password:112233<br /><br />Session I<br />What Causes Hunger? It's Not What You Think<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.wfpusa.org/drivers-of-hunger/">https://www.wfpusa.org/drivers-of-hunger/</a><!-- m --><br /><br />Questions:<br />1. “Conflict is the first driver of hunger in the world.”<br />Do you agree with this expression? Are there any episodes or news to share?<br /><br />2. “women are more likely than men to suffer from hunger and malnourishment. That’s because in many cases, women eat last and least.”<br />Do you know the possible reasons why women eat last and least in some countries?<br /><br />3. “In high-income countries, 40 percent of food is wasted.”<br />How often do you check your refrigerator? Is your refrigerator always full? Are you overbought? How do you manage your food purchases without wasting food?<br /><br />4. Do you buy expiring food at the supermarket? If not, why?<br />----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br /><br />Session II<br />Spain plans to control food waste – and all restaurants must offer ‘doggy bags’<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.spainenglish.com/2022/06/08/spain-plans-to-control-food-waste-and-all-restaurants-must-offer-doggy-bags/">https://www.spainenglish.com/2022/06/08 ... oggy-bags/</a><!-- m --><br /><br />Questions:<br />1. How do you judge this new draft bill? Can it effectively control food waste?<br /><br />2. Do you use dog bags to take leftover food home at a restaurant/wedding reception? Share your experience.<br /><br />3. Do you often cook? What do you do with leftovers? Do you usually eat leftovers at your next meal?<br /><br />4. Many people like to  prepare/order  so many dishes at meals or parties. Is it related to one's habits/culture?<br /><br />P.S.<br />1.參加三次(含實體及線上會議)後，只要繳交1,000元(學生500元)，即可成為ROYAL終身會員!<br />2.請帶著開放的心與熱情來參加全英文會話聚會!<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=38674">Louie Wang</a> — Fri Aug 12, 2022 4:14 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
